parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug ejection can cause loss of engine power, loss of control, and potentially lead to engine fires, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: spark plug blown out of cylinder head

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Camshaft position sensor failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and loss of control, potentially leading to accidents or strandings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and sidewall failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Power Steering Assist during Braking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power steering assist during braking can cause the steering wheel to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up when applying brakes
especially at low speeds; the vehicle wanders across the road; the steering system is rendered inoperable when full brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation can cause total steering loss, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Complete tread separation of the tire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydroboost system can cause the steering system to become inoperable during hard braking or emergency situations, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering system is rendered inoperable when full brakes are applied; the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up during braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the steering gearbox can cause the steering system to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering system is extremely difficult to turn
especially when the vehicle is first started or driven on a cold day; the steering wheel will stop at a half turn when the brake is applied.
